Implement a program to find the common elements in two arrays without using additional data structures.

Example:

```javascript
function findCommonElements(array1, array2) {
    // 1. Compare the first elements of the two arrays
    if (array1[0] === array2[0]) {
        // 2. If they are the same, compare the next elements, and so on
        if (array1[1] === array2[1]) {
            // 3. Repeat until all elements have been compared
            return [...new Set(array1) & new Set(array2)];
        } else {
            return null;
        }
    } else {
        return null;
    }
}
```

